properties.name: Burney Falls State Park
properties.segment: Launch point with time for waterfalls and a morale-reset before stepping onto the PCT.
properties.notes: Fly into Sacramento, drive ~4 hours to Burney and stage the car before heading to Round Valley.

properties.name: Round Valley Campground
properties.segment: Moderate gain with shade and a mellow first camp inside Lassen National Forest.
properties.notes: Plenty of water; good place to fine tune packs before deeper backcountry.

properties.name: Black Rock Camp
properties.segment: Gentle rollers through tall forest; famous for stargazing clearings.
properties.notes: Check the Halfmile notes for bear-hang trees—this site can be active.

properties.name: Horse Camp
properties.segment: Classic PCT singletrack with granite viewpoints; shared with pack stock in peak season.
properties.notes: Arrive early for tent pads near water.

properties.name: Indian Springs Camp
properties.segment: Water stop plus shaded camp. Keep an eye on spring flow by checking the PCT Water Report.
properties.notes: Backup: dry camp above the springs if flows slow down late season.

properties.name: Castle Crags Vista Camp
properties.segment: Steady climb rewarded by sweeping views of Castle Crags granite spires and Mt. Shasta.

properties.name: Castle Crags State Park
properties.segment: Massive descent into Castle Crags State Park with easy access to shuttles, STAGE bus, and Dunsmuir resupply.
properties.notes: Celebrate, resupply, then either head home or continue into Section P.

towns.name: Dunsmuir, CA
services: Access to STAGE bus, Amtrak Coast Starlight, and Mt. Shasta Taxi
towns.notes: Prime rest day between Castle Crags and Mt. Shasta. Pre-book shuttles during busy weekends.

transport.name: Sacramento Airport (SMF)
transport.notes: Fly in, rent car for 4-hour drive to Burney Falls

transport.name: Burney Falls Trailhead Parking
transport.notes: Stage car here or use Burney Taxi / Green Gables parking service

transport.name: Soda Creek Road Pickup
transport.notes: Exit point for STAGE bus or Mt. Shasta Taxi

transport.name: Sulphur Creek Camp (Dog Trail)
transport.notes: Alternate exit via Dog Trail—remote but shuttle accessible

transport.name: Flume Trailhead
transport.notes: Northern exit option; coordinate with trail angels or taxi

driveSegments.name: SMF → Burney Falls (I-5 + CA-299)
driveSegments.notes: I-5 North to Redding, then CA-299 East to Burney. Stop at Burney Falls State Park store for fuel + 5L water

driveSegments.name: Castle Crags → Dunsmuir (I-5)
driveSegments.notes: STAGE bus (limited schedule), Mt. Shasta Taxi, or trail angels via I-5
